properties.areaDesc: St. Marys River Point Iroquois to E. Potagannissing Bay
properties.headline: Gale Watch issued January 10 at 4:17AM EST until January 12 at 4:00AM EST by NWS Gaylord MI
properties.description:
* WHAT...Highest gusts up to 35 kt and highest waves around 6
feet possible.

* WHERE...St. Marys River Point Iroquois to E. Potagannissing
Bay.

* WHEN...For the SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY, until 6 AM EST early this
morning. For the GALE WATCH, from Saturday evening through
late Saturday night.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous highest waves which
could capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and highest
waves.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM EST EARLY THIS MORNING... ...GALE WATCH IN EFFECT FROM SATURDAY EVENING THROUGH LATE SATURDAY NIGHT
